To solve this problem using MATLAB, you need a list of animal names to work with. Since you want to find animals with names containing a single, non-repeating vowel, you can create a script to filter the list based on this criterion.

Below is a MATLAB script that demonstrates how you can achieve this. You'll need to input a list of animal names to get started. For demonstration purposes, I'll provide a small sample list, but you'll need to expand it based on your requirements.

```matlab
% Sample list of animal names
animalList = {'Tiger', 'Lion', 'Cheetah', 'Leopard', 'Panda', ...
              'Zebra', 'Giraffe', 'Kangaroo', 'Elephant', 'Penguin', ...
              'Koala', 'Crocodile', 'Flamingo', 'Peacock', 'Parrot'};

% Vowels to check
vowels = 'AEIOUaeiou';

% Initialize an empty cell array to store results
validAnimals = {};

% Loop through each animal name
for i = 1:length(animalList)
    name = animalList{i};
    vowelCount = zeros(1, length(vowels));

    % Count the occurrence of each vowel
    for j = 1:length(vowels)
        vowelCount(j) = sum(name == vowels(j));
    end

    % Check if exactly one vowel appears once
    if sum(vowelCount == 1) == 1
        % Find the vowel that appears once
        singleVowelIndex = find(vowelCount == 1);
        singleVowel = vowels(singleVowelIndex(1));

        % Check that this vowel is the only one in the name
        if sum(ismember(name, vowels)) == 1
            % Add to the list of valid animals
            validAnimals{end+1} = name;
        end
    end
end

% Display the valid animals
disp('Animals with a single, non-repeating vowel in their name:');
disp(validAnimals);
```

This script will output a list of animal names from your provided list that meet the criteria of having a single, non-repeating vowel. You can modify the `animalList` variable with a more comprehensive list of common animal names to get better results.

If you need more animals, consider expanding the list with common animals found in different regions or habitats, ensuring they are not rare or endangered. Remember, the effectiveness of this script depends on the comprehensiveness of your input list.
